                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.60D/100a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Finland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McClintock</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-24T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 24, 1943—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>74. You will delay action contemplated in my 72, April 23, 2 p.m. until further
                    instructions. Please acknowledge receipt of this message immediately stating
                    whether it was received in time.<note n="67" xml:id="d196fn67">In telegram No.
                        595, April 25, 10 a.m., the Chargé acknowledged receipt of the telegram and
                        said that he would cancel the appointment with the Finnish Foreign Minister
                        scheduled for that same day (124.60D/101).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
